Middle School 8th grade Volleyball with travel to Girard this Saturday, September 12th. Games will start at 9:00 am and be played at the HS.

Game Schedule:
East Court 9:00 SE vs Girard
West Court 10:00 SE vs Frontenac

-Games times can and may start earlier if a match is done early.
-No concessions will be available. Feel free to bring your own snacks and drinks.
-You must wear a mask the entire time and they will be conducting temp checks.
-You can only attend if you have a ticket. Each athlete will be given 4 tickets per family.

post_text:
Wowza! Thank you parents and community for supporting our “meet the staff”parade. We had a wonderful time and it was so good to see everyone.
We can’t wait to get the children back in school.

If you are bringing your child to school, pre-K through first grade, drop off your child off at the elementary wing. The second through fourth grade students need dropped off at the main 2 story building. Please drop your child off between 7:30 and 7:40, so they will have plenty of time to eat breakfast before class starts. For the first semester, breakfast will be free to all elementary students.

We will be taking the temperature of all the students and staff as they arrive and they will also sanitize their hands. Shortly after, the students will eat breakfast in their classrooms.

Please send your child with a backpack, mask, and water bottle.

It is so important, especially this year, to keep your phone number updated, so we can contact you in an emergency.

If you need anything, please call the office at 620-396-8211.

Thank you,
Mrs. Hall & Staff

post_text: Just a friendly reminder!
shared_text:
USD 247 Southeast Lancers
August 13 at 5:34 AM ·

Southeast Elementary School Update....

Parents and families can call SES on Thursday, August 13th, from 10:00 to 4:30 pm or next week to find out which homeroom your child will be in. The school number is 620-396-8211. The prek parents will be contacted by phone about the morning and after sessions.

SES back to school “parade” to meet the teachers....Please support the staff Thursday, August 20th, from 6:15-7:00 pm at SES as staff will be lined up on campus to wave at our school families as you drive by. PTO will be on hand to provide a treat for every SES student. Parents, students, families, and community are welcome to drive by, honk, and wave to show your support for the staff!

In addition to supplying masks for your child, please provide a water bottle as well when school starts on August, 21st

We hope to see everyone at the drive by parade on the 20th!

Thank you,
Mrs. Hall and Staff

post_text:
Please welcome Paris Stierwalt to the Lancer Family! Miss Stierwalt attended Pittsburg State University and graduated with a Bachelor in Education with a major of Family and Consumer Sciences and an emphasis in Interior Design. She spent her professional semester at Southeast High School and is excited to be back where she student taught! She will be teaching Family and Consumer Sciences to grades 8-12.

Miss Stierwalt recently became engaged to Justin Vratil. They have two rescue dogs and one cat. Their "zoo" is soon to be expanding, as they are adopting a black lab puppy that will grow up to be Justin's hunting partner.

Miss Stierwalt loves to antique shop, craft home decor signs, kayak, and walk nature trails with her dogs.

The Southeast High School Class of 2020 Commencement Ceremony will be held this Saturday, June 20th at 7:00 p.m.

Due to this being a closed/ticketed event with limited attendance, the event will also be live-streamed on this USD 247 Southeast Lancers Facebook page. Please share this information with any family/friends who do not have a ticket to attend in person, so they can tune in and watch the live video.

A friendly reminder for those who will be attending the ceremony in person, please abide by the recommended social distancing guidelines. Masks are encouraged.

Please be patient and respectful as the USD 247 staff members are working hard to make this event happen safely.

Congratulations to the Class of 2020! We are excited to honor you on Saturday!

shared_text:
SEK Interlocal #637
May 18 at 1:08 PM ·

Debbie McMurry, Southeast Middle School Paraprofessional
Debbie is retiring from the SEK Interlocal #637 after 20 years of service as a paraprofessional in the USD 247 school district. Debbie’s supervising teacher stated, “Deb has always been reliable and dependable. Her impact was lasting and reached well beyond the walls of Southeast Middle School. She was well loved by her students and school staff. She will be greatly missed!”

Ms. McMurry shared, “I have many great memories working with the students and teachers at Southeast Middle School for the past 20 years. My best reward was seeing the smile when a student got that answer correct that they struggled with. Their stories and smiles made my day.”

Thank you, Debbie, for your service to students, families, and the school community!

Southeast Elementary Parents and Families: You may return homework this week May 11th through the 14th from 7 AM - 2:30 PM. There will be a container in front of the elementary wing on the bench to put the homework inside of.

Report cards will be mailed out May 25th.

If you have a child that will be going into prek or kindergarten and did not get signed up for the roundups, please call the board office at 457-8350 Monday through Thursday, 8 AM until noon to get their name on the list. Please, help share the word.

None of us wanted to end the school year like this, but we made it! Thank you for supporting your child and the school! Our partnership makes a world of difference to the success of your child.

If you need us for anything, please contact us.

Keep safe!

Thank you,
Mrs. Hall and Staff

post_text: Supplemental education from Kansas Teachers coming to a Public Broadcasting channel near you. Here is a link to the Craw-Kan tv channel line up: https://ckt.net/wp-content/uploads/cktv.pdf
shared_text:
Kansas State Department of Education
April 17 at 9:46 PM ·

We are excited to announce that Kansas teachers, students and parents just got a new partner in their continuous learning efforts.

Thanks to the support of Kansas Public Broadcasters, Kansas students will receive supplemental education content by way of a new television program produced by Kansas PBS stations and KSDE, and hosted by local teachers. The new program called Learning Across Kansas will begin airing the week of April 20.

Each 30-minute segment, individually produced for elementary, middle school and high school students, will feature grade-specific educational content delivered by our very own Kansas teachers who serve on KSDE’s Continuous Learning Task Force.

Teachers, students and parents/caregivers, tune in for short, fun and engaging lessons. Plus, you just might see one of your own teachers presenting!

Learn more by visiting, https://www.ksde.org/Agency/Fiscal-and-Administrative-Services/Communications-and-Recognition-Programs/Learning-Across-Kansas

UPDATE TO SOUTHEAST FOOD SERVICE DISTRIBUTION (4/8/2020):

As a reminder, there will be no food service on Friday, April 10 (Good Friday) or Monday, April 13 (Easter Monday).

We will have a new food service schedule that will begin on Monday, April 20th. Under the new schedule, pick up and delivery times will occur on Monday through Thursday from 11:00 to noon. Multiple meals will be provided on Thursday to accommodate for Friday. We will no longer have a pick up at Southeast High School. Other delivery sites include:

◆ Southeast Middle School
◆ Southeast Elementary School
◆ Scammon (the old school, now a church)
◆ West Mineral (City Hall/Fire Department)
◆ Chicopee (Community Center)
◆ McCune School

*To schedule meals, please email Connie Kimzey at ckimzey@usd247.com

post_text:
I stumbled across this poem today and I thought it was fitting for what is upon us. Everyone please take care, give the kids a hug for us, and we will conquer this together!
Mrs. Hall and Staff

Unity

I dreamed I stood in a studio
And watched two sculptors there,
The clay they used was a young child’s mind,
And they fashioned it with care.

One was a teacher; the tools he used
Were books and music and art;
One a parent with a guiding hand,
And a gentle, loving heart.

Day after day the teacher toiled,
With touch that was deft and sure,
While the parent labored by his side
And polished and smoothed it o’er.

And when at last their task was done,
They were proud of what they had wrought,
For the things they had molded into the child
Could neither be sold nor bought.

And each agreed he would have failed
If he had worked alone,
For behind the parent stood the school,
And behind the teacher, the home.

(Poet unknown)
text:
I stumbled across this poem today and I thought it was fitting for what is upon us. Everyone please take care, give the kids a hug for us, and we will conquer this together!
Mrs. Hall and Staff

Unity

I dreamed I stood in a studio
And watched two sculptors there,
The clay they used was a young child’s mind,
And they fashioned it with care.

One was a teacher; the tools he used
Were books and music and art;
One a parent with a guiding hand,
And a gentle, loving heart.

Day after day the teacher toiled,
With touch that was deft and sure,
While the parent labored by his side
And polished and smoothed it o’er.

And when at last their task was done,
They were proud of what they had wrought,
For the things they had molded into the child
Could neither be sold nor bought.

And each agreed he would have failed
If he had worked alone,
For behind the parent stood the school,
And behind the teacher, the home.

(Poet unknown)

USD 247 Closed Monday, March 16 through Friday, March 20
text:
At the recommendation of the Commissioner of Education, Governor Laura Kelly, and the Speaker of the House, as well as our own concern for the safety and well-being of our students and families, we have made the decision that USD 247 schools will be closed Monday, March 16 through Friday, March 20. Effective immediately, all district events and extracurricular activities are canceled until the District reopens or further notice. [ 116 more words ]

post_text: Miss Gaddy is currently a Student Intern at Southeast High School!
shared_text:
Pittsburg State University - College of Education
March 10 at 1:25 PM ·

Meet Andrea Gaddy – she is currently pursuing a Master of Science degree with a major in school counseling. Gaddy, a Pittsburg native, is a Phi Kappa Phi member. She was inspired to pursue a school counseling degree by her mother, a special education teacher, and her older brother, an English teacher. Andrea said, “I wanted to become a school counselor so that I could make a similar difference in children's lives and help students reach their highest potential.” She is making an impact on young lives as an intern at Southeast High School. Gaddy plans to spend the summer traveling and is currently applying for counseling positions for the 2020-2021 school year. #makinganimpact

The Kindergarteners at SES celebrated 100 Days of School on Friday, February 7. Many activities were done throughout the day. Some included: counting the 100 items they brought, writing to 100, decorating a "100" crown, and filling out a poster regarding things like, ”If I had a $100.00, what would I buy?” “What will I look like in 100 years?” “I would like 100_____.” What a great day was had celebrating our 100th day of school!
http://usd247.com/2020/02/11/kindergarteners-celebrate-100-days-of-school/

On December 18, 2019, USD 247 received a $3,000 grant from the Community Foundation of Southeast Kansas. Dr. Miner, Superintendent, was presented with a check and a box of cookies from Harvey Dean, CEO and Founder of Pitsco, and Lisa Paterni, President of Pitsco in Pittsburg. This grant was provided by the Champions for Learners Fund. Dr. Miner commented, “We are very grateful to receive the grant and for the supporting partnerships we have with area businesses and organizations.” We would like to thank Pitsco and the Community Foundation of Southeast Kansas for their generous contribution.

The Kansas Association of Secondary School Principals (KASSP) has named Debbie Clawson, Southeast High School, as the KASSP Area II Assistant Principal of the Year. KASSP is an organization of over 450 secondary school principals from across the State of Kansas. Clawson was nominated and selected by peer principals. Candidates are evaluated on their school leadership, school improvement, dedication, professionalism, and service to students. Debbie was recognized at the 2019 KASSP Honors Reception on November 14 in Wichita. Congratulations, Debbie Clawson!
http://usd247.com/2019/11/14/local-school-administrator-honored/

USD 247 Southeast Lancers
October 6, 2019 at 5:15 PM ·

Southeast High School will host their annual Veterans Day Assembly on Friday, November 8th. Veterans and their spouses are invited to a breakfast at 9:00 a.m. in the SHS Cafeteria, followed by an assembly at 10:00 a.m. in the East Gymnasium, featuring music from the SHS band and choir. shared_text:
Eastern Kansas Sports
October 28, 2019 at 9:08 PM ·

Thank you to Jennifer Gardner for passing this along to us for USD 247 Southeast Lancers fans traveling to Osage City:
"For those coming to the Cherokee-Southeast vs Osage City game...the football stadium is on the southwest corner of town. We have some construction, but if you turn (head west) at Sonic, it'll take you through town and at the stop sign you turn left. We have a large parking lot and some parking near the visitors' side, too. Hope this helps, I know I hate not knowing where I'm going in a new town.

We do have a Sonic, Subway (west), Casey's (deli, etc, near Sonic), Pizza Hut (construction area), Buzzards Pizza (by Sonic), Marilyn's (burgers, steaks, etc, east side), Ridge Iron Grill (downtown and not blocked by construction), El Ranchito (west side by Subway), Jade Garden (west), plus the concession stand (usually burgers, hotdogs, walking tacos, etc)"
